      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"Swarm\" is a good way to put it, though it's more of a chemical cascade than a literal invasion of tiny, chaotic creatures. The hydrogen ions don't just randomly appear; they are the byproduct of the accelerated metabolic pathways kicking into overdrive when oxygen delivery lags behind the demand. Think of it like a sudden, overwhelming rush in a crowded, poorly ventilated room—the concentration of waste products (the $\\text{H}^+$ ions) spikes rapidly. This chemical imbalance disrupts normal muscle function, interfering with the contractile proteins, which is what causes the fatigue and the burning feeling.",
